[thinking] **Clarifying method registration**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm realizing that Class.getMethods can possibly be accessed without needing registration. In a native image, it seems like the getMethods function requires reflection metadata for classes. I'm curious about the TCK capturing active class coverage since that seems important. Also, when running natively, I wonder if the generated metadata should include methods for interfaces. It looks like the agent captures getMethods, which could be relevant. Let's dig deeper into this!
